<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 7:38PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Craig,
northern Rogers, southeastern Washington and southeastern Nowata
Counties through 815 PM CDT...
At 738 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Oologah, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Nowata...                         Chelsea...
Oologah...                        Talala...
New Alluwe...                     Watova...
Bushyhead...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
